      "heading": "Part I",
      "numbering": "restart",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "instructions",
          "text": "State the following theorems."
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Hölder’s inequality."
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Hahn Decomposition Theorem."
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Fubini Theorem for positive measures \\(\\mu\\) and \\(\\nu\\)."
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Monotone Class Theorem."
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Hahn–Banach Theorem."
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Monotone Convergence Theorem."
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The completeness of \\(L_E^1(\\mu)\\)."
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The theorem of uniform boundedness."
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "heading": "Part II",
      "numbering": "restart",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "instructions",
          "text": "Prove one of either Theorem 3 or 7 from part I."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "heading": "Part III",
      "numbering": "restart",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "instructions",
          "text": "Solve the following problems. In problems one through four \\((X,\\Sigma,\\mu)\\) is a measure space and \\(F\\) is a Banach space."
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Let \\(\\mathcal{F}\\subset\\Sigma\\) be a \\(\\sigma\\)-subalgebra. Prove the existence of the conditional expectation \\(E(f\\mid\\mathcal{F})\\) for \\(f\\in L_F^1(\\mu)\\)."
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Let \\(\\mathcal{R}\\) be a ring generating \\(\\Sigma\\) and suppose \\(f\\in L_F^1(\\mu)\\). Prove, if \\(\\int_A f\\,d\\mu=0\\) for each \\(A\\in\\mathcal{R}\\), then \\(f=0\\), \\(\\mu\\) almost everywhere."
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Suppose \\(E\\) (as well as \\(F\\)) is a Banach space and \\(U\\) is a bounded linear operator from \\(E\\) to \\(F\\). Show, if \\(f\\in L_E^1(\\mu)\\), then \\(U\\circ f\\in L_F^1(\\mu)\\) and\n\\[\n\\int U\\circ f\\,d\\mu=U\\int f\\,d\\mu.\n\\]"
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Suppose \\(X\\) is a locally compact Hausdorff space. Show, if \\(K\\) is a compact set and the restriction of \\(f\\) to \\(K\\), \\(f|_K\\), is continuous, then \\(f\\phi_K\\) is a Borel function. Here \\(\\phi_K\\) is the characteristic function of \\(K\\)."
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "problem",
          "problem": {
            "body": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Prove that \\(C([0,1])\\) is a closed proper subspace of \\(L^\\infty([0,1])\\) (the \\(L^\\infty\\) space with respect to Lebesgue measure on the interval \\([0,1]\\)). Explain how to view \\(L^1([0,1])\\) as a subspace of \\(L^\\infty([0,1])^*\\). Is \\(L^1([0,1])\\) a proper subspace of \\(L^\\infty([0,1])^*\\)?"
              }
            ],
            "subparts": []
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
